text.section:
Special courts-martial may be convened by:
Any person who may convene a general court-martial;
The commanding officer of a garrison, fort, post, camp, station, Air National Guard base, or naval base or station;
The commanding officer of a brigade, regiment, detached battalion, or corresponding unit of the Army;
The commanding officer of a wing, group, separate squadron, or corresponding unit of the Air Force; or
The commanding officer or officer in charge of any other command, when empowered by the adjutant general.
